(12704, 1, '2018-10-25 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Cannabis is slowly becoming widely accepted in society as many countries started to work towards the legalization of the plant. The USA and some other countries totally legalized recreational cannabis use and it\'s noticeable that it\'s driving a lot of tax money from tourism to improve the communities.  Many people started to grow their own cannabis since technology improved and the information is easily available on the internet. Today, there are so many different ways of growing your own cannabis and thousands of strains available.  Sometimes, it can be a tough task to decide which strain you should try to grow or smoke. The best way is to just experiment until you find the best suiting cannabis strain for you.  A very popular growing method in the last years is called cannabis cloning.  This method is very cheap and you get a plant with the desired characteristics.  If you\'re thinking that cloning might be something new for you in a growing career, then this guide is perfect for you!  <em>Keep reading as we\'re going to provide you with every bit of information required to grow your own cannabis clones.</em>  <hr />  <h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What is Cannabis Cloning?</strong></h2> <img class=\"size-full wp-image-1022 aligncenter\" src=\"https://weeducation.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/marijuana-clone.jpg\" alt=\"marijuana clone outdoors\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" />  In the last few years, there is a lot of information on cloning cannabis, and you probably heard many things about it.  You can clone any plant in the world, and we\'re so lucky that cannabis is just a plant like any other plant that has a root system.  Basically, cloning is choosing the plant with the right and desired characteristics, taking the part of it and growing another plant with the same genetics.  <em><strong>Does it mean you will have exactly the same plant?</strong></em>  No, it doesn\'t mean that your plant will look exactly the same when it comes to size and yield, but the characteristics will be identical. You need to be very selective when it comes to picking the plant you\'d like to clone. It\'s crucial that the plant is healthy and you like the characteristics when it comes to smoking.  We already mentioned that you\'re picking a small part of the plant and growing it as a separate plant. You cut a few stems from the mother plant (a plant you\'d like to clone) and then growing the rooting system of the clone until it isn\'t ready to grow on its own.  <em>In the following headings, we\'re going to provide you with details on each step of cannabis cloning!</em>  <hr />  <h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Things You Should Know About the Clones Before Starting</strong></h2> Cloning isn\'t a science, but even the most experienced growers fail with growing the clones sometimes.  <em>There are some things you should definitely know before deciding to start with cloning marijuana plants:</em>  <strong>Low costs of growing -</strong> We all know that cannabis seeds can be very expensive, so if you\'re on the budget, then having clones is the perfect thing for you. You just need a mother plant and you can cut as many clones as you want. It means you can produce as many plants as possible from just one plant. Such a huge money saving if you know what to do!  <strong>A clone is a copy of a mother plant - </strong>The clone won\'t be an exact copy of the mother plant and it won\'t grow to exact size, but it will be very close. The reason for it is that the clone starts without a root system and the root won\'t be huge as in the regular plant. Anything else, the characteristics of the buds and high will be the same. The perfect thing is that you will already know so much about the plant before cutting the clones, so you can be sure what kind of plant you can expect.  <img class=\"size-full wp-image-1021 aligncenter\" src=\"https://weeducation.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/cannabis-clone.jpg\" alt=\"cannabis plant in the flowering process\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" />  <strong>A quicker start in growing - </strong>Many people choose growing clones as they want to have buds faster. For instance, the clones will faster reach the size and development of the mother plant than the newly grown plants from the seed. If you don\'t have much time, then it\'s a perfect way as it can yield you some potent buds in a shorter period than usual.  <strong>You can cut the clones almost anytime - </strong>The great time with the clones is that you can cut them from the mother plant on almost any phase of the growth. Of course, you can\'t cut it when the plant is still in an early vegetative state, but after 4 weeks of growth, the plant is ready to yield some clones. Also, if you cut the clones from the bottom, the plant will create a root faster. The same goes for cutting from the top which will give you better results in the flowering phase.  <strong>Challenges in growing - </strong>Clones are not for everyone! You need to have a certain equipment and knowledge before growing clones. Also, if you think that you found your perfect strain, then just go for cloning! :)  <em>These are few important things you should have in mind before starting with growing cannabis clones. Now, we will share with you details that will help you in actually growing your own clones! </em>  <hr />  <h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Equipment You\'ll Need for Cloning</strong></h2> Basically, you don\'t need any equipment except the mother plant, scissors, and soil where you\'ll put your clones. You can improvise everything, but with improvisation comes the risk.  The equipment for cloning isn\'t expensive and you probably have all of that already at your home, so don\'t worry!  <strong>A healthy mother plant with proper genes - </strong>The mother plant is the prerequisite for growing your cannabis clones. Be sure the plant is perfectly healthy and that the gender is female. If you don\'t have a mother plant, you can find <a href=\"https://askmeaboutmarijuana.com/\">clones for sale</a> online and pick the right plant from a huge selection.  <strong>Sharp scissors - </strong>This is the equipment that can be found in almost every household. If you don\'t have it already, you should get one even if you don\'t think about cloning. These are used for trimming and are suitable for doing a perfect cut. Believe us, you don\'t want to mess your mother plant and clones because you don\'t have proper scissors!  <strong>Suitable starter cubes - </strong>It\'s important to have small cubes where you\'ll put your newly cut clones. The cubes will give enough space for the clones to create a healthy root system.  <strong>Root complex - </strong>It\'s not a required to have any root complex, but it will hugely help in creating the root system of your newly clones. In the beginning, the clones start without the root and they are very prone to illness. It\'s crucial to grow the root as soon as possible, so picking a root complex in a form of a gel or powder can be a smart investment.  <strong>A proper light system - </strong>You don\'t need a light if you\'re planning to grow clones outdoors. It\'s possible to do it, but it\'s very hard since outdoors\' conditions can be very rough for small plants without the root. We advise you to get CFL 150W and this light will do the job at the beginning stages of the clone growth.  <hr />  <h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>How to Cut a Clone From a Mother Plant?</strong></h2> <img class=\"size-full wp-image-1026 aligncenter\" src=\"https://weeducation.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/mother-cannabis-plant.jpg\" alt=\"Mother cannabis plant\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" />  Now when you have a basic idea what a cannabis cloning is and which equipment you need to have before starting the process, you\'re ready to start cutting the clones. In this part, we\'re going to provide you with the information on how to properly cut the clones from a mother plant.  First of all, before doing any cutting or modifying on any cannabis plant, you need to make sure that your cutting equipment is clean and disinfected. The small splash of water and dip in an ethyl alcohol will do the work.  If you\'re taking the clones from a mature plant, be sure that the plant is actually mature as you will just hurt the plant otherwise. Once you have many stems and leaves (usually after three weeks of vegetation), your plant is ready for taking clones.  <em>Here are the steps you should follow in order to get clones ready for putting in the soil:</em> <ul>          <li>Be sure that a mother plant is ready for cutting clones. Once you\'re sure, then you can prepare your starter cubes. Just put a bit of water a few minutes before putting the clones inside.</li>          <li>Once you\'re sure everything is ready, you\'re ready for the cutting. You should pick up the top of the plant from the new branch. Always cut in a 45-degree angle and don\'t take the clone that is longer than 20 cm. The reason for that is that the mother plant is going through a huge pressure and stress during cutting.</li>          <li>Always cut from the lower stems as these have a higher concentration of root hormones. Also, if you want the flowering process to be faster and yielding, then just cut the higher stems. Both will work well as you will need to nurture clones with many nutrients at the beginning.</li>          <li>When you cut the clone, it\'s time to put it in a water. You should do it immediately as the bubbles of air will start to collect in a cutting place and you want to prevent it as it will just hurt the root forming process.</li>          <li>Just leave the clones to sit for few minutes in the water until you\'re preparing a root gel or powder. Dip down your clones in the powder or gel (preferably both) and move them to started cubes.</li> </ul> <iframe width=\"764\" height=\"430\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/xFw3FObhuwQ\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>  Basically, that\'s it! It doesn\'t seem like a complicated process, right?  Just follow these steps and you will most likely be successful in making your own cannabis clones.  <hr />  <h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Nurturing Your Newly Cut Clones</strong></h2> <img class=\"size-full wp-image-1027 aligncenter\" src=\"https://weeducation.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/new-cannabis-clones.jpg\" alt=\"Nurturing newly cut cannabis clones\" width=\"1280\" height=\"851\" />  Once you successfully cut your clones and you put them inside started cubes, it\'s time to nurture them with enough nutrients, light, and humidity.  Since the clones don\'t have a root at the beginning, the plant needs to get the water and all the nutrients through the leaves. It means you need to spray the plants a few times per day with a water or keep the clones in a highly humid and warm environment.  If you\'re growing indoors, it can be easily done, but with outdoors just be sure that you\'re spraying with the water a few times per day and checking the condition of the plants often.  The perfect temperature for nurturing clones is around 24C which is not that hard to maintain indoors.  When it comes to lightning, many growers advise to use up to 150W CFL lamp since you don\'t need much energy for the new plants. The best light/dark setting would be 18/6 as the rooting system grows the best when there is a small amount of darkness involved.  For outdoor growers, just be sure that you\'re growing the clones in the right period of the year with the long days and short nights.  <hr />  <h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>8 Crucial Tips to Grow Your Cannabis Clones Successfully</strong></h2> Many people started with growing their plants from the clones since this method has many benefits. The only problem is that people usually fail to bring their clones from the beginning stage to the flowering stage.  <em>If you\'re following our guide, then you shouldn\'t have any problem, but still, there are 8 crucial steps you need to be aware of all the time when growing cannabis plant from the clones:</em> <h3><strong>1) Pick the Healthy Mother Plant</strong></h3> <img class=\"size-full wp-image-1029 aligncenter\" src=\"https://weeducation.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/healthy-mother-plant.jpg\" alt=\"Healthy mother plant\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" />  The biggest reason most growers fail in growing their marijuana plants from the clones is the bad genetics of the mother plant. It\'s the most crucial step to pick the right cannabis plant which you will clone.  We already talked about the importance of genetics and that the clone will have totally identically genetics and characteristics as a mother plant, so why not to put enough time to decide and pick the right plant?  We advise to always wait till an early flowering stage as you will be able to tell the gender of the plant. You want to take the clones from a female plant only!  Also, if you\'re waiting till the early flowering stage, the plant will be very resistant to stress and you will be able to tell about the health and condition of it. <h3><strong>2) Humidity Is the Key!</strong></h3> Remember that newly cut clones don\'t have a root system! You can\'t nurture them through the soil, so it\'s important to always keep the humidity high. You should always check your plants if they are wet! Spraying them with the water a few times per day will do the work!  Just avoid spraying the plant in the middle of the day if you\'re growing outdoors since the sun can definitely burn the clones that are very prone to any kind of sickness.  Also, to keep the humidity levels high, you can use plastic bags and cover the clones with it. That will keep the humidity high all the time, so you don\'t need to worry all the time about spraying the clones. <h3><strong>3) Provide Your Clones With Enough Nutrients</strong></h3> <iframe width=\"764\" height=\"430\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Xw83XVRVdTw\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>  When you starting out with the cannabis clones, the plants won\'t have a root system which means you need to provide many nutrients to enhance the root development.  The best nutrients you can use to grow healthy root systems are B-1 and potassium. Also, don\'t forget to use root complex powders or gels that will boost the growth of your clones.  You can also use the regular flowering nutrients at the beginning that have high concentrations of phosphorus.  Just remember to always use 1/2 or 1/4 of the amount you would usually use for the plants you\'re growing from the seed. <h3><strong>4) Cut the Clones From the Bottom Parts of the Mother Plant</strong></h3> <iframe width=\"764\" height=\"430\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/MNtEaKslYes\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>  Always be sure that you\'re cutting from the bottom of the healthy plant for the fastest development of the root system. The reason for that is a high concentration of root growth hormones that can be found in the stems that are located on the bottom of the plant.  When you have a healthy mother plant, you don\'t need to worry much as you can literally cut any part of it. If you decide to cut from the upper part of the plant, it\'s also fine since the flowering process will be much faster.  If you\'re not using any equipment and root complex nutrients, then just cut the bottom part as it will be a challenge to grow the root and healthy clone without any nutrients for root growth. <h3><strong>5) Prepare a Mother Plant for the Cloning Process</strong></h3> Cutting the parts of the plant is a huge stress for any plant in any stage of development, so it\'s crucial to prepare the plant for the stress.  The best way is to grow the plant until you can see the gender. Start with the flowering nutrients few weeks before cutting the plant. You should use less nitrogen for few weeks before cutting and add more phosphorus as it will give your clones a head start in growing a root system. <h3><strong>6) Always Cut More Then You Need</strong></h3> That is a general rule in growing cannabis, especially growing clones. Always take more than expected as there is a huge possibility that you will mess up something or clones simply won\'t perform as expected.  If you have more clones than expected, you can throw stagnant plants and just focus on clones that are performing well!  <hr />  So, now you know how to do cannabis cloning right way! Just follow the tips and advice we provided you in this guide and you\'ll be fine!  Let\'s grow your favorite cannabis strains in an unlimited number and enjoy the high! :) <h3><strong><em>Have any questions or suggestions? Please share your thoughts in the comment section! </em></strong></h3>', 'Ultimate Guide on Cloning Marijuana Plants', 'TODO: Write Excerpt\r\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2018-10-25 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://localhost/vietnam_chronicles/?p=12704', 0, 'post', '', 0);
